<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Cull" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Cull,</orth> to pick out, to select from many: <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.234" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 234</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 98</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.274" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 274</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 3, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 40</bibl>. Followed by <emph>from</emph>: <cit><quote>--ed these fiery spirits from the world,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.114" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 114</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.75" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 1, 44</bibl>. By <emph>out of</emph>: <cit><quote>ye familiar spirits that are --ed out of the powerful regions under earth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 10</bibl></cit>. Joined with <emph>forth</emph>: <cit><quote>Fortune shall c. forth out of one side her happy minion,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.391" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 391</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. the infected forth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 4, 43</bibl></cit>. With <emph>out</emph>: <cit><quote>do you now c. out a holiday?</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 54</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>